node.text:
either go after it or shut up about it⚡️ 
-
get that kiss of cool without the the overly dull ashy tones with the matte series 
-
matte series is a brown to tan background and a blue to green reflect to help reduce unwanted warmth 
-
this works perfect in a root shade to create an iridescent natural finish… my favorite to mix with the matte series is N for a neutral cool sandy finish and NW for a touch of warmth

node.text:
that bitch with the good mane⚡️ 
-
-
-
the goal for this chick was to brighten around the hairline and dust the crown with some subtle softness to make the grow out more softer… because guess what, she only comes twice a year 👀
-
HAIRLINE: 
i created brightness by parting diagonal back working to the crown… this allows color to splash forward and leaves no heavy lines 
-
CROWN:
i dusted the top with subtle brightness. i took a thin section off the part and laid in horizontal sections underneath to never see the regrowth

want a subtle hair line? it’s all in the mane way ↓
-
-
-
first things first, create ribbons on the hairline for a softer more natural grow out
-
then I take diagonal back sections from the points on the hairline, this way the natural depth falls behind each ribbon for the blondes to pop
